\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Setting up the checker\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The core logic of the hackathon is protected in a compiled file. You must "activate" the one that matches your Operating System.\
\pard\tx566\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Navigate to the 
\f2\fs26 checkers/
\f1\fs24  folder.\

\f0\b Windows Users:
\f1\b0  Find the file for Windows, rename it to 
\f3\b\fs26 checker.pyd
\f1\b0\fs24 , and move it to the main folder (where 
\f2\fs26 executable.py
\f1\fs24  is).\

\f0\b Linux Users:
\f1\b0  Find the file for Linux, rename it to 
\f3\b\fs26 checker.so
\f1\b0\fs24 , and move it to the main folder.\
\pard\tx566\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 macOS Users: 
\f1\b0 the 
\f3\b\fs26 checker.so 
\f1\b0\fs24 already provided in the main folder is the right one.\
\
NOTE: If you cannot see any extensions, just name the file \'93checker\'94.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

